OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Tue 30 Jun to Thu 9 Jul
OL,6,FFairly changeable conditions at first
OL,7,Fwith periods of rain and showers, and
OL,8,Fthere could be some thundery outbreaks
OL,9,Fat times. The best of the drier and
OL,10,Fbrighter weather initially will be
OL,11,Facross the southeast. Then perhaps a
OL,12,Fdrier start to July for many, although
OL,13,Fthe northwest may still see some rain
OL,14,Fat times, and perhaps accompanied by
OL,15,Fsome strong winds. Temperatures are
OL,16,Flikely to be near average in the north
OL,17,Fand slightly warmer than average in
OL,18,Fthe south, but with winds generally
OL,19,Ffrom the west temperatures aren't
OL,20,Fexpected to be as hot as seen recently.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
